According to <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85058140/1910-11-19/ed-1/seq-4/" rel="nofollow">The Salt Lake herald-Republican., November 19, 1910, Page 4</a> Column 2 &amp; 3, William Thaw 3d was a nephew of Harry Kendall Thaw, the murderer of Stanford White. His wife was the former Gladys Virginia Bradley, a sister of Mrs. Anthony J. Drexel Biddle (Cordelia Rundell Bradley).

See also <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn84026749/1911-02-10/ed-1/seq-3/" rel="nofollow">The Washington times., February 10, 1911, Last Edition, Page 3</a>, col. 1, &quot;WILLIAM THAW III IS MISSING AGAIN - Young Millionaire Disappears While on Honeymoon In Jamaica.&quot;

Another photo of her in <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030214/1919-09-14/ed-1/seq-37/" rel="nofollow">New-York tribune., September 14, 1919, Page 3</a>
